General.Name: Cardiex Ltd
General.Description: CardieX Limited, a commercial-stage digital healthcare company, uses its medical devices to redefine the way hypertension, cardiovascular disease, and other vascular diseases are clinically diagnosed and managed in the Americas, Europe, and the Asia Pacific. Its SphygmoCor XCEL is a vital signs and vascular biometric monitoring device that offers non-invasive assessment of the central aortic pressure waveform, including pressures and indices of arterial stiffness and providing noninvasive measurement of arterial pressure that the heart, brain, and kidneys experience. The company focuses on developing CONNEQT Pulse, a connected vascular biometric monitor; CONNEQT Band, a wearable cuffless device to monitor vascular health in patients, as well as to provide general health insights; CONNEQT App, a part of the digital ecosystem for its CONNEQT devices; CONNEQT patient management portal; CONNEQT Cloud, which empowers its Arty Heart Health analytics platform and data repository for its CONNEQT Portal and CONNEQT App; and CONNEQT Touchpoint to incorporate its technology across an ecosystem of consumer and connected fitness devices, smartphones, and computers. It sells its cardiovascular devices and services to hospitals, clinics, research institutions, and pharmaceutical companies. The company was formerly known as AtCor Medical Holdings Limited and changed its name to CardieX Limited in June 2018. CardieX Limited was founded in 1994 and is based in Sydney, Australia.
